pass125 golden - fj-lax: specialize U32 radix sort to four byte passes
target=eval/sort_64k_u32; sort_along_axis_literal_radix U32 path
lever=U32 radix keys only contain four significant bytes, so the stable LSD radix path uses four byte passes for DType::U32 and keeps the existing eight-pass helper for all 64-bit/float/signed literal radix users.
fixture=1000 element U32 vector from radix_sort_u32_ascending_matches_unsigned_reference: i%7 maps to 0, u32::MAX, 1, i%5 duplicates, or ((i*2654435761) wrapping xor i). Axis dimension is 1000 so the radix path is taken.
golden_blob=v1 bytes: b"fj_lax_sort_u32_four_pass_v1\0" + ascending sorted U32 values as little-endian u32 + ascending argsort as little-endian i64 + descending sorted U32 values as little-endian u32 + descending argsort as little-endian i64.
