isomorphism=U32 ascending keys are exactly the unsigned value. For descending, key xor u64::MAX leaves all high bytes equal for U32 and reverses the low 32 bits, so four low-byte passes induce the same total order as eight passes. LSD radix is stable, preserving original index tie order for sort and argsort. Floating-point and RNG are not involved.
